## SOLID Principles

### Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)

Each class has one responsibility:

```csharp
// Event processor - handles business logic
public class SuscripcionCreadaProcessor : IRequestHandler<SuscripcionCreada, ProcessResult> { }

// Repository - handles data access
public class SuscripcionRepository : ISuscripcionRepository { }

// Hosted service - handles SQS polling
public class SqsQueueConsumerService<T> : IHostedService { }
```

### Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP)

```csharp
public class SuscripcionCreadaProcessor : IRequestHandler<SuscripcionCreada, ProcessResult>
{
    private readonly ISuscripcionRepository _repository;
    private readonly IUnitOfWork _uow;
    
    public SuscripcionCreadaProcessor(ISuscripcionRepository repository, IUnitOfWork uow)
    {
        _repository = repository;
        _uow = uow;
    }
}
```

## Coding Standards

### Event Naming Convention

Events follow the pattern: `evt-{squad}-{entity}-{verb-past}`

```csharp
// Event class name (PascalCase)
public class SuscripcionCreada : IRequest<ProcessResult>
{
    public Guid Id { get; set; }
    public string ClienteId { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
}

// Event name for logging/configuration
// "evt-susc-suscripcion-creada"
```

### Queue Naming Convention

Queues follow the pattern: `{product}-{env}-sqs-{event}`

```
suscripciones-prod-sqs-ventas-alta
suscripciones-stg-sqs-cobranzas-resultado
suscripciones-qa-sqs-facturacion-cambio
```

Dead Letter Queues add `_dlq` suffix:
```
suscripciones-prod-sqs-ventas-alta_dlq
```

### Language Requirements

All code, comments, and messages MUST be in English:

```csharp
// Good
_logger.LogInformation(">>> Processing SuscripcionCreada: Id={Id}", @event.Id);
throw new InvalidOperationException("Subscription already exists");

// Avoid
_logger.LogInformation(">>> Procesando SuscripcionCreada: Id={Id}", @event.Id);
throw new InvalidOperationException("La suscripción ya existe");
```

